<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">−</td>
  <td class="diff-deletedline"><div>'''Operation ''Varsity''''' (24 March 1945) was a successful joint <del class="diffchange diffchange-inline">American–British</del> [[airborne forces|airborne]] operation that took place toward the end of [[World War II]]. Involving more than 16,000 paratroopers and several thousand aircraft, it was the largest airborne operation in history to be conducted on a single day and in one location.{{#tag:ref|The airborne component of [[Operation Market Garden|Operation ''Market Garden'']] was a larger operation, but the drop zones were split over three distinct areas and spread over several days. Operation ''Varsity'' was conducted on a single day in one location, and as such, is the largest single airborne operation in history.&lt;ref name="Devlin615"/&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Smith, p. 126&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Rawson, p. 17&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Harclerode, p. 551&lt;/ref&gt;|group="Note"}}</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">+</td>
  <td class="diff-addedline"><div>'''Operation ''Varsity''''' (24 March 1945) was a successful joint <ins class="diffchange diffchange-inline">American, British and Canadian</ins> [[airborne forces|airborne]] operation that took place toward the end of [[World War II]]. Involving more than 16,000 paratroopers and several thousand aircraft, it was the largest airborne operation in history to be conducted on a single day and in one location.{{#tag:ref|The airborne component of [[Operation Market Garden|Operation ''Market Garden'']] was a larger operation, but the drop zones were split over three distinct areas and spread over several days. Operation ''Varsity'' was conducted on a single day in one location, and as such, is the largest single airborne operation in history.&lt;ref name="Devlin615"/&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Smith, p. 126&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Rawson, p. 17&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;Harclerode, p. 551&lt;/ref&gt;|group="Note"}}</div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"><div>Part of [[Operation Plunder|Operation ''Plunder'']], the effort by the British [[21st Army Group]] under [[Field Marshal (United Kingdom)|Field Marshal]] [[Bernard Montgomery]] to cross the [[Rhine River]] and from there enter [[Northern Germany]], ''Varsity'' was meant to help the 21st Army Group to secure a foothold across the Rhine River in western [[Germany]] by landing two [[airborne forces|airborne]] divisions on the eastern bank of the Rhine near the village of [[Hamminkeln]] and the town of [[Wesel]].</div></td>
  <td class="diff-marker">&#160;</td>
  <td class="diff-context"><div>Part of [[Operation Plunder|Operation ''Plunder'']], the effort by the British [[21st Army Group]] under [[Field Marshal (United Kingdom)|Field Marshal]] [[Bernard Montgomery]] to cross the [[Rhine River]] and from there enter [[Northern Germany]], ''Varsity'' was meant to help the 21st Army Group to secure a foothold across the Rhine River in western [[Germany]] by landing two [[airborne forces|airborne]] divisions on the eastern bank of the Rhine near the village of [[Hamminkeln]] and the town of [[Wesel]].</div></td>
</tr>

